claims:
1. A method of processing written words in a visual prosthesis comprising:
providing a visual prosthesis including a camera video processor and stimulation system;
recording a scene with the camera and transferring data representing the scene to the video processor;
scanning the data for patterns representing written characters;
converting the written characters to braille characters; and
presenting the braille characters to a user through the stimulation system.

13. A visual prosthesis comprising:
a camera;
a video processing unit receiving visual data from the camera, processing the visual data to produce stimulation patterns; and
an implantable stimulation system receiving stimulation patterns from the video processing unit suitable to stimulate neural tissue with the stimulation patterns;
means in the video processing unit for scanning the visual data for patterns representing written characters;
means in the video processing unit for converting the written characters to braille characters and including the braille characters in the stimulation patterns
